<p><i><b>Rock until You Drop</b></i> is the first full-length album by the British <a href="/wiki/Heavy_metal_music" title="Heavy metal music">heavy metal</a> band <a href="/wiki/Raven_(British_band)" title="Raven (British band)">Raven</a>, released in 1981. The album was the first of many heavy metal studio albums issued by British <a href="/wiki/Independent_label" title="Independent label" class="mw-redirect">independent label</a> <a href="/wiki/Neat_Records" title="Neat Records">Neat Records</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> It reached position No. 63 in the <a href="/wiki/UK_Albums_Chart" title="UK Albums Chart">UK Albums Chart</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>The song "Lambs to the Slaughter" was covered by German thrash band <a href="/wiki/Kreator" title="Kreator">Kreator</a> on their <i><a href="/wiki/Out_of_the_Dark_..._Into_the_Light" title="Out of the Dark ... Into the Light">Out of the Dark ... Into the Light</a></i> EP, added to the re-mastered <i><a href="/wiki/Terrible_Certainty" title="Terrible Certainty">Terrible Certainty</a></i> CD in 2000.</p>
<p></p>
